            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/chee-231" class="program-course-title">
              CHEE 231 Data Analysis and Design of Experiments (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-20180" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Chemical Engineering (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/609">Faculty of Engineering</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Chemical Engineering              : Foundation of the design and execution of experiments based on statistical principles and of the results analysis. Topics: Data visualization, significant digits; uncertainty, precision, accuracy, propagation of uncertainty; univariate data analysis, normal distribution; sampling distribution and point estimates, confidence intervals, hypothesis testing; simple and multiple linear regression; design of experiments.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Pierre-Luc Girard-Lauriault (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>(3-2-4)</li>
              <li>Corequisite: CHEE 291</li>
              <li>Restriction: Not open to students who have taken CHEE 392</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
