                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/chee-510" class="program-course-title">
              CHEE 510 Advanced Separation Processes (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-20250" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Chemical Engineering (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/609">Faculty of Engineering</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Chemical Engineering              : Introduction to thermodynamics of ideal multicomponent vapour-liquid equilibrium concepts; distillation of multicomponent mixtures; numerical solution of the MESH equations (mass balances, equilibrium expression, components, summations and enthalpy balances) for distillation columns operating under realistic conditions; introduction to non-ideal thermodynamics; gas absorption; simulation using commercial process simulation software.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Jeff Gostick (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>(3-0-6)</li>
              <li>Prerequisite(s): CHEE 351</li>
              <li>Restriction: Restricted to Chemical Engineering students</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
